This paper deals with the verification of safety properties in artificial neural networks, which is a topic closely related to machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses the potential failures of ANNs in safety-critical systems, which falls under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR). The use of bounded model checking and symbolic verification is a technique commonly used in control systems (cs.SY) and programming languages (cs.PL). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG, followed by cs.SE, cs.CR, cs.SY, and cs.PL.
